    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Boards that generally consist of two panels (usually hinged), used with game pieces that are moved as determined by throws of the dice. The boards typically have twelve holes along the base of each side, used for scoring. Similar to "backgammon boards."</Note_Text>
